# Frontend: TypeScript must compile

When you change code under `frontend/`, run the TypeScript compiler and fix any errors before considering the work done or checking in.

## Do this

From `frontend/`:

```bash
yarn tsc --noEmit
```

Fix all reported errors. Prefer patterns already used in the codebase (e.g. narrow `asyncUser.result` with `asyncUser.result && asyncUser.result.data` rather than optional chaining on a `false | AxiosResponse` union).

## Do not

- Leave frontend changes without running `yarn tsc --noEmit` when TypeScript types or components were touched.
- Assume the dev server or linter alone caught type errors.
